property.name: text
property.value: This model measures the power spectrum of bandlimited noise and compares it against the theoretical value of the spectrum. Notice that the sidebands decay slightly more slowly than the theory predicts because of aliasing distortion. You can experiment with the bandwidth of the noise.

property.name: text
property.value: This submodel uses a DE Director so that there is buffering in the receivers, and then, inside the _intance_ of the Periodogram actor, there is an SDF director to handle the multirate properties of the spectrum analysis. If you use Open Actor to look inside the Periodogram, you will not see the SDF director. If you use Open Instance, you will.
